			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Damage shields should multiply their damage by both the percentage slowed and by the number of mage damage shields on the same player.
<br />

<br />

<br />
eg:   Mage casts flamey shield on main tank, shield does 50 pts per hit.
<br />
Shaman slows mob by 75%, shield now does 50 * 1.75 = 88(rounded up) to that slowed mob.
<br />

<br />
If Mage # 2 casts the same ds on that tank, it increases the base damage before slow calc by a factor of 2.  Base ds is now 100, and with 75% slow on the mob, it will be hit for 100 * 1.75 = 175.
<br />

<br />
For fun, say you had 1 warrior, 1 cleric, 1 shaman, and 3 mages, you cold have the tanks damage shield doing 50*3(1.75) = 263 points.   In a raid situation, with (not going to happen <img src="images/smiles/icon_razz.gif" alt="Razz" border="0" />) 10 mages, that would ramp up to 875 per hit   <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="Smile" border="0" />  
<br />

<br />
It unfortunately would involve the game engine having to calculate ds damage by that formula for each slowed mob that hits the tank, each time they hit (in case slow wore off or was overwritten), based on % it is slowed by, and somehow buff stacking multiple copies of the same spell all in one icon or something.
<br />

<br />
Unworkable idea, yes, but maybe someone can get a better idea from it?<br />_________________<br />Kyril - 58th level High Elf Magician
<br />
Now with Skittles!</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
