				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">The idea of stacking damage sheilds sounds interesting, and would certainly increase the desireability of multiple magicians.  Unfortunatly, I'm not sure there are enough of us out there to truely make this usefull (Well, on Rodcet anyways, high end magicians are very rare, we have maybe 20 active ele flagged mages).  But I also like the reflecting thing.  I think if you made it scale as mobs hit for less, it would not be overpowering.  Like, have a maximum 20% damage reflection; but also increase the 61 damage sheild to  a maximum ~75pts.  This would at the same time be a nerf to the newbies being PL'd with damage sheild, which is something I think Sony dislikes (I hate PL'd newbies as well).  I think its a fair exchange.  Increased mage DPS, more widespread use of our DS (maybe...just maybe I'd get MGB!), and makes multiple magicians more desirable.  Sounds good to me!
