				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">The damage prevention thing doesn't make any sense from a "flaming shield that burns people who attack me" perspective, and it's too late in the game to make such a ground-breaking change.
<br />

<br />
I've always though that damage shields should work on each *attack*, however, and not just on hits, and if the attack *does* hit it should do full damage, whereas it should do partial damage if its a miss.
<br />

<br />
The messages would have to be compiled into a per-tick damage message though (or somesuch), otherwise damage shields would cause insane numbers of messages -- even more then they already do.  The effect (-hp) could still be applied instantly.<br />_________________<br />Arhallia Ironborne
<br />
