<br />

<br />
how about a new spell line that allows you to imbue elemental energy into weapons/pets?  similiar concept to all the weapon summons you get in the early levels.  those were usable by other classes but except at the very very early stages of the game, nobody would use them since they had better weapons.
<br />

<br />
a line of spells that add elemental proc effects, say starting in the low teens/twenties and scaling up to 65.  maybe 20 DD at the low end and 200 at the high end, could even have different procs for different elements like Fire could be a DD, earth could be a DD+stun, water could be a heal like blessing of the knight, Air could be a neg hate proc (concussion of air).  
<br />

<br />
anti PL code is already in place so you can't cast the lvl 65 version on newbs in East commons, and procs are unaffected by haste/slow so don't have to worry about things like that limiting there usefulness.  Would give you some group utility and raid usefulness, aslong as it takes more than 1 mage to keep it up on a raid.  (done via recast times and not done via mana intensiveness)  Duration should be decent, 45 min or more so its not a hassle.
<br />

<br />
Rangers and knights already have a line of self buffs that add procs, enchanters are capable of adding small lifetap procs via their illusion: other spells.  theres a handful of items that allow warriors and such to do the same.  codes already in place so its not difficult to add.  make the mage spell version more desirable than those already available.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=754455" target="_blank" class="postlink">Elder Xuthaz Everhate</a>
